The paper deals with the secure transmission in wiretap channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of statistical channel state information (CSIT) is also a common theme in communication networks (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the scaling behavior of the secrecy capacity, which is a topic in stochastic processes and optimization (cs.SI).
